{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857059941,"sessionID":"ses_286ac78b7ffeF0NyDeA7x9pwnO","part":{"id":"prt_d7953ff27001LUcg0eoh5HjwXI","messageID":"msg_d7953ea99001AVJM6K8G7OoLAU","sessionID":"ses_286ac78b7ffeF0NyDeA7x9pwnO","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_2d52ac9a0a1b4974a5f19a63","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/picod  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Configuration (auth_config.go)\n\n- [ ] **T001** Create `pkg/picod/auth_config.go` with `AuthConfig` struct containing:\n  - `PublicKeyPath` string (optional, for file-based key loading)\n  - `PublicPaths` []string (comma-separated paths exempt from auth)\n  - `AllowQueryParam` bool (enable token via ?token=)\n  - `JWTIssuer` string (expected issuer claim)\n  - `JWTAudience` string (expected audience claim)\n\n- [ ] **T002** Add environment variable loading functions:\n  - `LoadAuthConfigFromEnv() (*AuthConfig, error)`\n  - `GetPublicPathsFromEnv() []string`\n  - `GetBoolEnv(key string, defaultValue bool) bool`\n\n- [ ] **T003** Add validation for AuthConfig (Validate() error)\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: Enhanced Middleware (auth_middleware.go)\n\n- [ ] **T010** Create `pkg/picod/auth_middleware.go` with enhanced middleware:\n\n- [ ] **T011** Implement public path checking:\n  - `isPublicPath(path string, publicPaths []string) bool`\n\n- [ ] **T012** Implement query parameter token extraction:\n  - Extract token from `?token=` query parameter when enabled\n\n- [ ] **T013** Implement issuer/audience validation:\n  - Validate `iss` claim if configured\n  - Validate `aud` claim if configured\n\n- [ ] **T014** Implement error response standardization:\n  - Add `error_code` field to error responses\n  - Match pkg/router/jwt_middleware.go patterns\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: AuthManager Enhancements (auth.go)\n\n- [ ] **T020** Add dynamic public key reload method:\n  - `ReloadPublicKey() error` - reload from environment variable\n\n- [ ] **T021** Add SIGHUP signal handler support:\n  - `StartKeyRotationWatcher()` - listen for SIGHUP and reload key\n\n- [ ] **T022** Add error code constants:\n  - `ErrCodeMissingHeader = \"AUTH_MISSING_HEADER\"`\n  - `ErrCodeInvalidFormat = \"AUTH_INVALID_FORMAT\"`\n  - `ErrCodeInvalidToken = \"AUTH_INVALID_TOKEN\"`\n  - `ErrCodeTokenExpired = \"AUTH_TOKEN_EXPIRED\"`\n  - `ErrCodeKeyNotConfigured = \"AUTH_KEY_NOT_CONFIGURED\"`\n\n---\n\n### Phase 4: Server Integration (server.go)\n\n- [ ] **T030** Update `NewServer()` to accept AuthConfig parameter\n\n- [ ] **T031** Update route registration to use public paths:\n  - Configure `/health` as public by default\n  - Apply public path filter in middleware\n\n- [ ] **T032** Register SIGHUP handler for key rotation\n\n---\n\n### Phase 5: Testing (auth_config_test.go, auth_middleware_test.go)\n\n- [ ] **T040** Create `pkg/picod/auth_config_test.go`:\n  - Test LoadAuthConfigFromEnv with valid config\n  - Test LoadAuthConfigFromEnv with missing required fields\n  - Test GetPublicPathsFromEnv parsing\n  - Test GetBoolEnv with various values\n\n- [ ] **T041** Create `pkg/picod/auth_middleware_test.go`:\n  - Test isPublicPath matching\n  - Test query parameter token extraction\n  - Test issuer/audience validation\n  - Test error response format with error_code\n\n- [ ] **T042** Update existing `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`:\n  - Add tests for ReloadPublicKey()\n  - Add tests for SIGHUP key rotation\n\n---\n\n### Phase 6: Build & Verify\n\n- [ ] **T050** Run `go build ./cmd/picod` - verify build succeeds\n\n- [ ] **T051** Run `go test ./pkg/picod/...` - verify all unit tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T052** Run `go vet ./pkg/picod/...` - verify no vet errors\n\n- [ ] **T053** Run `golint ./pkg/picod/...` (if configured) - verify linting\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- **T001**: None (new file)\n- **T002**: T001\n- **T010**: T001, T002\n- **T011**: T010\n- **T012**: T010\n- **T013**: T010\n- **T014**: T010\n- **T020**: auth.go (existing)\n- **T021**: T020\n- **T022**: T020\n- **T030**: T010, T014\n- **T031**: T030\n- **T032**: T021\n- **T040**: T002\n- **T041**: T010\n- **T042**: T020\n- **T050**: All implementation tasks\n- **T051**: T040, T041, T042\n- **T052**: T050\n- **T053**: T050\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY | Yes | - | PEM-encoded RSA public key |\n| PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_PATHS | No | /health | Comma-separated paths that skip auth |\n| PICOD_AUTH_ALLOW_QUERY_PARAM | No | false | Enable token via ?token= query param |\n| PICOD_JWT_ISSUER | No | - | Expected JWT issuer claim |\n| PICOD_JWT_AUDIENCE | No | - | Expected JWT audience claim |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md`\n- Proposal: `proposal.md` (AR-017)\n- Existing: `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n- Existing: `pkg/picod/server.go`\n- Reference: `pkg/router/jwt_middleware.go`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go\">\nERROR [15:2] \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/watch\" imported and not used\nERROR [66:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [81:9] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [95:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} 